<h1>Girl and Boy Scout Program</h1>

<p>A Naturalist-led, two-hour Field Trip Program at Woldumar is $4.00 ($3.00 Woldumar Members) per scout with a minimum of $50.00 per group. A one-hour Traveling Naturalist presentation is $3.75 ($3.00 Woldumar Members) per scout with a minimum of $50.00 per group plus a $.68 per mile (over 10 miles round trip) mileage fee. Add an additional hour to any of our programs for $25. All fees are due on the day of the program. All programs do include time outdoors, so be sure to dress for the weather!</p>

<p>To register for a program call the Woldumar office at (517) 322-0030 Monday through Friday, between 10:00 a.m. and 5:00 p.m. Scout programs can generally be scheduled after school during the evening or on Saturdays. Please have your preferred dates and times, the program topic as well as the number of scouts ready when you call. </p>

<p>If you can't find what you're looking for, we'd be happy to design a program that meets your needs. Simply let us know what you're covering and we will work with you and the Girl/Boy Scout Handbooks to develop a program that helps you reach your goals. Additional fees may apply. Call for more information. </p>

<p>Remember that we can help you earn your Badges, Try-its, Arrow Points or Ranks but you'll have to contact your local Girl or Boy Scout office to purchase badges for your scouts. </p>

