<h2>Opportunities for Boy Scouts at Woldumar</h2>

<h3>Trip Preparation</h3>
<p>Woldumar is the perfect place to prepare for many of your scouting trips. Our property is a great site to practice your skills and prepare for the adventures that lie ahead. With 150 acres and almost 5 miles of trails, your troop can come out to Woldumar and prepare for several badges. <p>

<h3>Historical Education</h3>
<p>Woldumar also provides a unique experience for those who wish to learn about life long ago. Scouts can visit our historic Moon Log Cabin built in the 1860's and glimpse Michigan's pioneer past. This historic dwelling is a great place to investigate while working on these badges or awards. </p>

<h3>Field Studies</h3>
<p>Woldumar also offers opportunities for field studies. Explore our property and its diverse habitats to observe wildlife, identify plants, or detect signs of environmental damage. Venture out to our wetlands, forests and prairie for the perfect place to work on numerous badges. </p>

<h3>Service Projects</h3>
<p>Woldumar is a private, non-profit organization and keeping our 188-acre nature preserve up and running takes a lot of effort and hard work. Woldumar depends on volunteers to help accomplish many of these tasks. Some volunteers arrange to provide their services on an individual basis. There are also several events throughout the year where many volunteers combine their efforts. If your scouts need an entire project, Woldumar could use your help! Your scouts' ingenuity and effort here at Woldumar can help them earn awards and ranks in these areas. </p>

<h3>Community Program Information</h3>
<p>At Woldumar Nature Center we offer some super seasonal programs! Our community programs and events offer a wide variety of information covering topics on everything from American heritage to survival skills. Keep an eye out for these fun and fascinating programs that could provide the knowledge you need for many of your badges.</p>